.TH "create_hyp_mappings" 9 "create_hyp_mappings" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
create_hyp_mappings \- duplicate a kernel virtual address range in Hyp mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" create_hyp_mappings
.BI "(void *from "  ","
.BI "void *to "  ","
.BI "enum kvm_pgtable_prot prot "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "from" 12
The virtual kernel start address of the range
.IP "to" 12
The virtual kernel end address of the range (exclusive)
.IP "prot" 12
The protection to be applied to this range
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The same virtual address as the kernel virtual address is also used
in Hyp-mode mapping (modulo HYP_PAGE_OFFSET) to the same underlying
physical pages.
